-- Blackstone Group eyeing Intelsat: report
-- 
-- Mon Apr 16, 2007 8:45pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/17/us-intelsat-blackstone-idUSN1636058420070417

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The world's largest commercial satellite operator Intelsat is up for sale and has been approached by the Blackstone Group, according to a report on the Wall Street Journal Web site on Monday. 

 Intelsat, controlled by a private equity consortium, purchased PanAmSat Holding Corp. last year for about $3.2 billion. Intelsat's private equity owners, which include Apax Partners Inc., Apollo Management, MDP Global Investors, are seeking an equity value of $6 billion for the company, according to the report citing unnamed sources. Representatives for Intelsat and the Blackstone Group were not immediately reachable.